Saudi British Fourth-Quarter Loan-Loss Provisions Fall 67%

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-02-19T07:51:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-19/saudi-british-fourth-quarter-loan-loss-provisions-fall-67-.html
  Saudi British Bank , the lender 40
percent owned by  HSBC Holdings Plc , said provisions for bad
loans in the fourth quarter fell 67 percent from the year-
earlier period.  Provisions declined to 238 million riyals ($63.5 million)
in the three months ended Dec. 31, from 714 million riyals a
year earlier, according to data posted on the  Saudi bourse 
website today.  On Jan. 16, Saudi British said fourth-quarter profit rose
to 397 million riyals from 26 million riyals a year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at   shajimathew@bloomberg.net  